# <!-- BEGIN AUTH SERVICE -->
#
# Auth Service
#
# Purpose
# - Provide authentication and tenant-scoped authorization for all API routes.
# - Produce a stable AuthContext for downstream services (AuditTrail, Integrity, Agents).
# - Enforce tenant isolation as an invariant: handlers must not trust tenantId from the client
#   when it can be derived from auth/session.
#
# Core invariants
# - Every request that mutates tenant data must run behind auth middleware.
# - tenantId is derived from the authenticated principal (token/session), not from request body/query.
# - Authorization checks must be explicit and capability/role based.
# - Security-relevant actions should emit audit events via AuditTrailService.logImmediate.
#
# AuthContext contract (minimum)
# - principalId: string
# - tenantId: string
# - roles: string[]
# - scopes/capabilities: string[]
# - sessionId: string | null
# - requestId: string
#
# Request flow
# 1) Authenticate: verify bearer token / session cookie; validate signature & expiry; resolve principal + tenant
# 2) Authorize: enforce tenant access and capability/role gates
# 3) Attach context: req.auth + requestId
# 4) Audit: denied requests -> authz_denied; privileged actions -> audited with target metadata
#
# Middleware surface (recommended)
# - requireAuth
# - requireTenant
# - requireCapability(capability)
#
# Handler rules
# - Never authorize using tenantId from client input.
# - Use req.auth.tenantId as source of truth and reject conflicts for diagnostics.
#
# Integration points
# - AuditTrailService: log authz denies and privileged grants.
# - Integrity endpoints: derive tenant/session from AuthContext; record resolution to VMRT + audit.
# - Agent endpoints: tenant-scoped execution; reasoning steps persisted to audit trail.
#
# Testing guidance
# - 401 for missing/invalid token
# - 403 for tenant not accessible
# - cross-tenant access denied
# - denies emit audit events with requestId + principalId
#
# <!-- END AUTH SERVICE -->
